                    <ul class="cs-signs">
                        <li class="cs-sign">
                            <h3 class="cs-sign-title">Bare Dirt Yard or Thin Turf</h3>
                            <p class="cs-sign-text">Dead spots, compacted caliche, and patchy grass are signs that your turf was never installed correctly or isn’t the right variety for southern New Mexico’s heat.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="cs-sign">
                            <h3 class="cs-sign-title">Dead Plants Every Season</h3>
                            <p class="cs-sign-text">Replacing the same shrubs year after year gets expensive. The real fix is choosing species that actually handle Las Cruces’s alkaline soils and 100°F+ summers.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="cs-sign">
                            <h3 class="cs-sign-title">Overgrown and Out of Control</h3>
                            <p class="cs-sign-text">Shrubs blocking windows, trees crowding your roofline, and beds buried under weeds all hurt curb appeal. A professional reset brings order back to your yard.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="cs-sign">
                            <h3 class="cs-sign-title">New Build or Blank Slate</h3>
                            <p class="cs-sign-text">New construction lots need proper grading, amended soil, and a cohesive planting plan. Piecemeal trips to the garden center rarely produce lasting results in this climate.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
